message: Hello! Thank you for contacting Better Deal Insurance. My name is Chris. How can I assist you today?
I am so angry right now! Your company is a total nightmare to deal with.
I'm deeply sorry to hear that you're feeling this way. Could you please let me know what seems to be the issue so I can assist you better?
I don't have time for this! I've been trying to get my claim sorted for weeks and no one has helped me.
I apologize for any inconvenience this may have caused you. Before proceeding, can you confirm your full name, date of birth, first line of address, and postcode for security purposes?
This is ridiculous! My name is John Doe, date of birth is 01/01/1980, first line of address is 123 Main Street, postcode 12345.
Thank you for completing security. I understand your frustration, John. Let me see how I can help you with your claim.
Finally! It's about time someone took me seriously.

I completely understand your feelings, John. It sounds like a really rough situation. A possible resolution could be escalating your claim for urgent processing. Would you prefer to proceed with that?
Yes, that's what I've been asking for all along. Why couldn't the other agents do that?
I apologize for any disappointment you've faced before. I'm glad that I was able to help you today. We'll get this escalated for you. Is there anything else you would like to address?
No, that should be all. Thank you for finally listening to me.
You are welcome, John. I'm glad we could find a way forward. If you need any further assistance, please don't hesitate to reach out. Have a great day!
